.SH NAME
goal_in_my_reservation \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" goal_in_my_reservation
.BI "(struct ext2_reserve_window *rsv "  ","
.BI "ext2_grpblk_t grp_goal "  ","
.BI "unsigned int group "  ","
.BI "struct super_block * sb "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rsv" 12
inode's reservation window
.IP "grp_goal" 12
given goal block relative to the allocation block group
.IP "group" 12
the current allocation block group
.IP "sb" 12
filesystem super block
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Test if the given goal block (group relative) is within the file's
own block reservation window range.

If the reservation window is outside the goal allocation group, return 0;
grp_goal (given goal block) could be -1, which means no specific
goal block. In this case, always return 1.
If the goal block is within the reservation window, return 1;
otherwise, return 0;
